<br />
The Free Peoples (30)<br />
<br />
The Overall point of this deck is to make smeagol really big, discard all the minions, and set up to do it again. <br />
Condsider the following situation(This is perfect cond. it will probably never be this good).<br />
You have your four companions. Frodo has Sting and a cloak, Merry Has an Escape and Hobbit Sword. There are four Countrysides out, four everyone knows, And you have 2 or 3 not listening in your hands and some don&#39;t follow the lights. <br />
Imagine the biggest minion you can, and assign him to Smeagol. Let&#39;s use Sauron for this example. Assign the other minions wherever- EXCEPT ON MERRY. If he has to fight, assign the weakest minion to skirmish him, and go to him first. Next go to smeagol. Merry is (with everyone knows) a 13. Exert Boromir twice to make Merry a 17. Exert Merry twice to make smeagol +17. Discard Frodo&#39;s Cloak or exert Frodo using 9-fingered frodo to remove a burden, which in turn heals 4 wounds with countryside. Guess what. Heal Merry 2x and Boromir 2x and repeat. You can then add usually about 8 burdens to make smeagol str + 16. Then you can exert Frodo 5x to make him str +10. Then if you have another 9-fingered frodo, heal and go another str+17. So far you&#39;re at 80 str. Sauron is overwhelmed twice over. When you win, use not listening to remove all those burdens, say 6 of them. That&#39;s 24 wounds you can heal. Use Don&#39;t follow the lights to discard the rest of the minions. Move on.<br />
Now, More Practically, Assign a small minion to Smeagol and use Don&#39;t Follow the Lights on the bigger minion.  This deck has only lost once, out of about a hundred, and that is because I did not draw a single country sides. <br />
       Good Luck, and please tell me what you think </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
